A MASSIVE search for a wanted man is continuing in Glasgow. Hunt for dangerous fugitive continues A MASSIVE search for a wanted man is continuing in Glasgow.Jonathan Kelly, 34, was recently freed from Low Moss Prison, Bishopbriggs, and has failed to report to police.Detectives are working to unravel a network of associates in the city suspected of harbouring the dangerous fugitive.Officers believe he has been supported by friends who have helped him remain a step ahead of police.As the search continues, the officer leading the manhunt urged Kelly to hand himself in.It comes after armed police, acting on intelligence, swooped on a Glasgow street.But following a seven-hour operation, Kelly was nowhere to be found.Detective Inspector Ian Hylands said: &quot;I would appeal to Kelly to give himself up and contact police with a view to handing himself in.&quot; 